## 3. Protocol Alignment

### ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) — Primary
- **Crate:** `agent-client-protocol` (Rust)
- **Spec:** RESTful — `/agents`, `/agents/{name}`, `/runs`, `/runs/{run_id}`
- **Used for:** Sessions, modes, streaming, multimodal content
- **Source:** <https://agentcommunicationprotocol.dev>

### A2A (Agent-to-Agent) — Secondary
- **Discovery:** `/.well-known/agent.json` (AgentCard)
- **Task lifecycle:** Submitted → Working → InputRequired → Completed/Failed/Canceled
- **Source:** <https://agent2agent.info>

### Design Decision: ACP primary, A2A for discovery
Both protocols are under **Linux Foundation** governance. Goose bridges both via `formats.rs` (parsing/generation) and `A2ARegistrySource`.

