### 2.5 Tool Filtering — How Modes Restrict Tools (`tool_filter.rs` + `reply_parts.rs`)

The tool filtering pipeline in `prepare_tools_and_prompt()`:

```
All tools from ExtensionManager
    │
    ├── code_execution filter: if active, keep only first-class extension tools
    │
    ├── MODE FILTER: active_tool_groups from routing decision
    │   └── ToolGroupAccess::Full("developer") → keep developer tools
    │   └── ToolGroupAccess::Full("none") → keep nothing
    │
    ├── SCOPE FILTER: hide orchestrator-only extensions when not in orchestrator context
    │
    ├── EXTENSION FILTER: allowed_extensions from routing/slot binding
    │   └── If not empty, only keep tools from listed extensions
    │
    └── Sort alphabetically (stable prompt caching)
```

### 2.6 The Reply Loop — Where Routing Meets Execution (`agent.rs` L852-1583)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> HandleElicitation: User message
    HandleElicitation --> ExecuteCommand: Not elicitation
    ExecuteCommand --> AutoCompact: Not a command
    AutoCompact --> ReplyInternal: Compaction done/not needed
    
    state ReplyInternal {
        [*] --> PrepareContext
        PrepareContext --> StreamFromProvider
        StreamFromProvider --> CategorizeTools: Response chunk
        CategorizeTools --> DispatchTools: Has tool calls
        CategorizeTools --> AccumulateText: No tool calls
        DispatchTools --> PermissionCheck
        PermissionCheck --> ExecuteTools: Approved
        PermissionCheck --> WaitApproval: Needs approval
        WaitApproval --> ExecuteTools: User approves
        ExecuteTools --> SaveMessages
        AccumulateText --> SaveMessages
        SaveMessages --> StreamFromProvider: More turns
        SaveMessages --> [*]: Exit (no tools + no retry)
    }
    
    ReplyInternal --> [*]: Stream complete
```

**Key events emitted during the loop:**
- `AgentEvent::Message(msg)` — Every response chunk, tool result
- `AgentEvent::ModelChange {model, mode}` — Lead-worker model switching
- `AgentEvent::RoutingDecision {...}` — Emitted by server, not agent itself
- `AgentEvent::McpNotification(...)` — MCP server notifications
- `AgentEvent::HistoryReplaced(conversation)` — After compaction

