## 🔑 Key Architectural Patterns

### 1. Agent Loop (`Agent.reply()`)
```
User Message → OrchestratorAgent.route() → RoutingDecision
  → Agent.reply(conversation, tools, system_prompt)
    → Provider.complete() / Provider.stream()
    → ToolRequest? → ExtensionManager.call_tool() → ToolResponse
    → Loop until text response or max_turns
  → Stream AgentEvents (Message, McpNotification, RoutingDecision)
```

### 2. Provider Trait
```rust
pub trait Provider: Send + Sync {
    fn get_name(&self) -> &str;
    async fn complete_with_model(...) -> Result<(Message, ProviderUsage), ProviderError>;
    async fn stream(...) -> Result<MessageStream, ProviderError>;
    fn get_model_config(&self) -> ModelConfig;
    // + fetch_supported_models, generate_session_name, etc.
}
```

### 3. Extension System (MCP)
- **Builtin:** DuplexStream in-process (developer, memory, etc.)
- **External stdio:** spawn process, communicate over stdin/stdout
- **External HTTP:** Streamable HTTP MCP transport
- **Platform extensions:** todo, apps, chatrecall, extensionmanager, summon (in-process Rust)

### 4. Data Flow: Desktop ↔ Server
```
Electron → HTTP POST /reply {user_message, session_id}
  → SSE stream of AgentEvents
  → Desktop renders incrementally
OpenAPI spec generated via: just generate-openapi
```

